<section class="principles">
  <div class="principles-inner">
    <div class="principle-quote">
      <blockquote>
        <p>The moment you receive a payment, the tax is already set aside — before you make a single decision about what to do with it. That's not a feature. That's a behavioral system. Most people who fail at self-employed taxes don't fail at math. They fail at not spending the money before it's due.</p>
      </blockquote>
    </div>
    <div class="principle-note">
      <p>HoldQuarter is built on that insight. Not a calculator. Not a reminder. A system that removes the decision entirely — so the money is always there when the IRS expects it.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>